theorem interior_diff_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hB : IsClosed B) :
    interior (A \ B) = interior A \ B := by
  -- We show mutual inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction.
    intro x hx
    -- `x` lies in `interior (A \ B)`, hence in `A \ B`.
    have h₁ : x ∈ A \ B := (interior_subset : interior (A \ B) ⊆ A \ B) hx
    -- From this we get `x ∈ A` and `x ∉ B`.
    have hxA : x ∈ A := h₁.1
    have hxNB : x ∉ B := h₁.2
    -- Monotonicity of `interior` yields `x ∈ interior A`.
    have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A :=
      (interior_mono (Set.diff_subset : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
    exact ⟨hxIntA, hxNB⟩
  · -- `⊇` direction.
    rintro ⟨hxIntA, hxNB⟩
    -- Let `U = interior A`. It is an open set containing `x` and contained in `A`.
    set U : Set X := interior A
    have hU_open : IsOpen U := isOpen_interior
    have hU_sub  : (U : Set X) ⊆ A := interior_subset
    have hxU     : x ∈ U := by
      simpa [U] using hxIntA
    -- Consider the open set `V = U ∩ Bᶜ`, which still contains `x`.
    have hV_open : IsOpen (U ∩ Bᶜ) := hU_open.inter hB.isOpen_compl
    have hxV     : x ∈ U ∩ Bᶜ := by
      have hx_notB : x ∈ Bᶜ := by
        -- `hxNB : x ∉ B`, which is exactly `x ∈ Bᶜ`.
        simpa using hxNB
      exact ⟨hxU, hx_notB⟩
    -- `V` is contained in `A \ B`.
    have hV_sub : (U ∩ Bᶜ : Set X) ⊆ A \ B := by
      intro y hy
      have hyU  : y ∈ U := hy.1
      have hyNB : y ∈ Bᶜ := hy.2
      have hyA  : y ∈ A := hU_sub hyU
      exact ⟨hyA, by
        -- `y ∈ Bᶜ` translates to `y ∉ B`.
        simpa using hyNB⟩
    -- By the characterization of interior, `x ∈ interior (A \ B)`.
    exact (interior_maximal hV_sub hV_open) hxV
